  "text": "According to the predictions of our photometric model in the ground calibration configuration, the 300 K eccosorb emission should contribute a background level of 3.18 pW/pix (see [CITATION_1] ). This value agrees well with the measured value measured of 3.24 pW/pix. Figure 8 shows the spatial distribution of the polarization angle ψ and polarization fraction p derived from fitting the background intensity variations with HWP position, using Eq. 2. The fit was performed independently for the TRANS and REFLEX focal planes which observe the same direction. As a consequence, the spatial distribution of the polarization angle is similar on the two focal planes.",
